miflu with your MD, be sure to notify him/her within 48 hou\u2026"

lang=en

text:            "text": "PSA #2: If YOU develop flu symptoms, and you want to discuss Tamiflu with your MD, be sure to notify him/her within 48 hours of the onset of symptoms. Only your MD can diagnose the flu, and Tamiflu is most effective when started within that window."

lang=en

text:            "text": "If you begin to have real flu symptoms (not just a common cold), get medical care and take anti-flu medications (Tamiflu or Relenza) asap.  Taken within 48 hrs of beginning of symptoms, they shorten the duration and severity of illness.  Could save your life. https://t.co/ppFLCybwqh"

lang=en

text:            "text": "PSA: If someone in your household has come down with the flu, let your MD know. Sometimes they can prescribe Tamiflu to reduce the chances of others in the household contracting the virus."
